description: Two US lawmakers, Senator Maria Cantwell and Representative Cathy McMorris Rodgers, have agreed on draft data privacy legislation to limit data collection by tech companies and empower Americans. The legislation includes oversight of personal data use, disclosure requirements for data transfers, and FTC enforcement.
title: US lawmakers reach bipartisan agreement on data privacy legislation

description: An overcrowded makeshift ferry sank off the north coast of Mozambique, leading to the tragic loss of 91 lives. The boat, unfit for passenger transport, was carrying 130 passengers to an island in Nampula province. Misinformation about cholera and challenging sea conditions contributed to the disaster.
title: More than 90 killed as boat sinks off Mozambique coast

description: Former finance commission chiefs suggest GST rationalization, real-time data importance, and asset-creating infrastructure investments for policymakers dealing with economy changes. Kelkar, who headed the 13th Finance Commission, underlined the need to rationalise the GST structure and move to a single rate mechanism, something that was recommended by the panel ahead of the key tax reform.
title: Ex-finance commission panel chiefs raise key economic issues

description: Wipro's swift leadership change contrasts with LTIMindtree's deliberate CEO succession planning. Nachiket Deshpande's US relocation influences his candidacy. Phil Fersht endorses him for the role amidst Chatterjee's $10B growth goal.
title: Internal candidates in race for top job at LTIMindtree

description: Mark Zuckerberg overtakes Elon Musk as the third-richest globally, with Musk slipping to fourth due to Tesla's stock decline. Zuckerberg's net worth is $186.9 billion, behind Bernard Arnault and Jeff Bezos.
title: Zuckerberg richer than Musk for 1st time since 2020

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi criticized the INDI Alliance for lacking vision and credibility, highlighting internal conflicts and uncertainty about leadership. He questioned the alliance's ability to choose a leader, mentioning Rahul Gandhi's ambiguity on PM candidate selection. Modi emphasized their disarray and struggle to present a united front, creating political uncertainty for the upcoming elections.
title: INDIA bloc a den of corrupt, anti-national people: Modi

description: Higher cocoa prices are affecting companies across the board, including dairy major Amul, ice cream brand Baskin Robbins, snacking and cereal company Kellanova, and others. Amul is looking to hike the price of its chocolates by 10-20%, Jayen Mehta, MD at Gujarat Cooperative Milk Marketing Federation (GCMMF), which owns the brand, told TOI.
title: Amul chocolates may get costlier as rising cocoa prices bite

description: Uttar Pradesh CM Yogi Adityanath criticizes Congress for terrorism, corruption, and neglecting Hindu sentiments. Praises PM Modi's development initiatives and military actions. Emphasizes 'New India' under Modi's leadership. Highlights BJP's governance, security, and cultural preservation efforts. Urges public support for upcoming elections.
title: Congress fed biryani to terrorists while poor starved: Yogi in Rajasthan

description: Thierry Delaporte's tenure at Wipro saw a significant share price increase but faced challenges in revenue growth and senior executive dissatisfaction. External leadership recruitments and restructuring efforts impacted company culture and stability.
title: 'Delaporte could not energise Wipro's India base from Paris'

description: RBI emphasized that recurrent inflation shocks caused by climate change can undermine policy transmission and need stricter monetary policies. According to RBI's monetary policy report, climate change has potential to increase inflation and impede GDP. It said global average temperatures are rising, with an accompanying increase in extreme weather events, and the economic and social impact is becoming increasingly evident.
title: Climate change can stoke inflation, stunt growth: RBI

description: The Congress Manifesto 2024 proposes job and education quotas in the private sector to fulfil UPA-era promises. A 'diversity commission' will oversee diversity, with a focus on SC/ST/OBC categories. The manifesto emphasizes inclusivity in corporate hiring and private education, aiming for social justice and equitable opportunities.
title: Cong's quota vow aims to fulfil long-standing promises

description: Chhattisgarh HC grants custody of a 9-year-old girl to her father, prioritizing her well-being. The child expressed a strong desire to live with her father due to a nurturing environment, despite allegations of abuse by her mother.
title: 9-year-old call mom ‘negligent’, HC gives her custody to dad

description: Former cabinet minister and three-time MLA, Dinesh Agarwal, switched from Congress to BJP citing lack of leadership in Congress and praising PM Modi. Representing Dharampur seat, he criticized Congress leadership and was suspended for six years for 'anti-party activities' after joining BJP.
title: Fresh blow for Cong as U'khand ex-minister quits party, joins BJP

description: Maneka Gandhi accepts BJP's decision not to nominate son Varun for Pilibhit, emphasizing BJP's cadre-based nature. Jitin Prasada announced as Varun's replacement. Maneka expresses pride in Varun's potential contribution and vows to serve Sultanpur. Varun pledges continued service to constituents. Both emphasize dedication to public service and welfare.
title: Neither surprised nor upset over ticket denial to Varun: Maneka

description: BJP President J P Nadda lauds Modi govt for implementing beneficial schemes for marginalized sections, women, farmers, and youth in Tamil Nadu. He criticized corrupt opposition parties and highlighted the impact of initiatives like PM Garib Kalyan Anna Yojana. Nadda undertook a roadshow in Trichy and supported BJP's candidate in Ariyalur.
title: Nadda holds TN road show after HC nod, tears into opposition bloc

description: Delhi finance department highlighted DJB's fund misuse and debt to Supreme Court. Special audit revealed fund diversion and financial statement absence, risking penalties. Various departments showed low spending compared to budget estimates.
title: DJB got 28,400cr since '15-16, but 'no accountability', fin dept to SC

description: The ongoing elections in Uttarakhand have led to a surge in demand for buses and cabs during the peak wedding season, causing challenges for families in booking vehicles for baraats. State authorities have diverted over 12,000 vehicles for election duty, affecting wedding preparations and creating logistical dilemmas.
title: Wedding crasher: Polls in peak shaadi season trigger taxi rush

description: Union Minister Rajnath Singh advocates 'One Nation, One Election' at a Bikaner rally, aiming to enhance Indian democracy by aligning local and national elections. Singh praises PM Modi's global impact and highlights India's increasing influence under his leadership. He dismisses religious tension claims within BJP, citing international recognition for Modi.
title: Rajnath Singh bats for 'One Nation, One Election' at Bikaner rally

description: Women account for a very small proportion of candidates and MPs. In 1962, the year consistent gender data for voters, candidates, and MPs were available, 42% of voters were women. By 2019, this had risen to 48.2%, nearly equal to their share of the population. However, only 9% of all candidates were women.
title: Women seen as voters, not candidates; WB hospitable, K'taka worst

description: Former Maoist rebels in Chhattisgarh, like Atami, find peace and new opportunities after surrendering arms. They embrace family life, new careers, and community support, leaving behind the fear and violence of their insurgent past.
title: After their farewell to arms, former Maoists find life of peace

description: The Orissa High Court issues notice to the state government following a PIL by activist Narayan Chandra Jena, addressing concerns about government doctors' private practice affecting healthcare quality in state-run facilities. Jena urges the court to establish a monitoring committee and proposes a ban on private practice with non-practising allowance for doctors.
title: HC notice to Odisha on plea to ban private practice by government doctors

description: The Allahabad high court has ruled that 'Kanyadaan' is not required for the solemnisation of a marriage under the Hindu Marriage Act. Only 'saptapadi' (the Sanskrit for'saat phere') is an essential rite of such a marriage, observed the Lucknow High Court bench while hearing a revision appeal filed by Ashutosh Yadav.
title: 'Kanyadaan' not essential under Hindu Marriage Act: HC

description: The Himachal Pradesh High Court has instructed the state government to settle pending dues of the Loktantra Prahari Samman Yojana, a scheme providing honorarium to individuals imprisoned during the Emergency. The court ruling emphasizes the need for releasing 'Samman Rashi' to petitioners and highlights the government's actions regarding the Act's repeal.
title: Court asks HP to pay Emergency scheme allowance till guv signs bill

description: The Delhi High Court will review LN Mishra's grandson's plea for a new investigation into his grandfather's assassination at Bihar's Samastipur Railway Station over 48 years ago. Vaibhav Mishra challenges the High Court's decision for a fair CBI investigation, highlighting concerns about justice and accountability. The upcoming review aims to shed light on the case's complexities.

description: PM Modi criticized Trinamool Congress for lawlessness in Bengal, highlighted attacks on central agencies. He condemned Mallikarjun Kharge for disrespecting J&K security personnel's sacrifices, contrasting BJP's development vision with Congress's appeasement politics.

description: An election flying squad intercepted three individuals aboard a train at Tambaram station, confiscating 4 crore cash. The trio, including a BJP worker, had their bags filled with currency notes seized, leading to investigations into their connection to the upcoming elections.
title: Rs 4cr cash seized from 3 persons at Tambaram railway station in TN

description: The Supreme Court of India forms a 7-member expert committee to identify the critical habitat of the endangered Great Indian Bustard (GIB) and recommend a ban on overhead power lines. Emphasizing conservation and renewable energy, the court aims for a balance between development and preservation. India's renewable energy goals align with global sustainability targets.

description: The Supreme Court struck a delicate balance between the country's drive to transition from fossil fuel-based electricity to renewable energy and protection of the highly endangered Great Indian Bustard (GIB) in a first-ever judgment recognising the dangers of climate change and supporting India's ambitious international commitment to achieve 'zero emission' by 2070.

description: The Times of India wins the green brand of the year title at the IAA Olive Crown Awards 2024 for prioritizing environmental causes. Their initiatives 'Saving Our Stripes' and 'UnPlastic India' gained global recognition, with the #UnplasticIndia campaign receiving support from UNEP and Dia Mirza.

description: The Bombay High Court overturned a 1997 collision as not an 'act of God', directing compensation to the deceased car owner's family. Both drivers were found equally negligent in the accident. The court considered negligence over 'process of elimination' and awarded Rs 10 lakh compensation despite expenses exceeding.

description: An engineer was booked after mentioning a bomb at Bengaluru Airport. Sanjay Pai faced FIR based on an airline staff's complaint. Detained and interrogated, he claimed a bomb in his bag, later released, citing irritation from frisking levels.

description: British runner Russ Cook completes epic 16,000km journey across Africa in 352 days, facing challenges like theft and injury. Despite setbacks, he persevered, reaching northern Tunisia. description: Banerjee accuses NIA of local residents' 'attack'. NIA refutes, cites unprovoked assault. Investigation into crude bombs, explosion. Mob hinders searches, arrests. Aggressive crowd obstructs legal procedures.

description: A suicide bombing in northwest Pakistan targeted a convoy of Chinese engineers heading to a construction site, resulting in the deaths of five Chinese nationals, including a female engineer. The incident highlights security challenges faced by foreign workers in the region.

description: On its 45th anniversary, right before the Lok Sabha elections, the outlawed Ulfa (I) asked that New Delhi create a conducive environment for serious conversation in order to reach an agreeable political resolution. description: 24-year-old woman arrested with friends for fatally stabbing 28-year-old Ranjit Rathod in Nagpur after an altercation captured on CCTV at a pan shop. The incident has shocked the local community.

description: Chennai Customs summons Ponguleti Harsha Reddy for involvement in purchasing Rs 1.7 crore smuggled watches from Hong Kong dealer via intermediary. Delayed appearance due to dengue. Investigation ongoing with potential value exceeding Rs 100 crore.

description: Driven by rising demand in India and China, graduate management education is poised for a watershed moment, with 40% of students worldwide focusing on developing AI capabilities. title: Protests in Balochistan over hospital privatization proposal
Defamation trial involving Bruce Lehrmann reopened

description: A 28-year-old man identified as Nicholas Metson, from Shuttleworth House in Lincoln, stabbed his wife, Holly Bramley to death, cut her body into more than 200 pieces  and dumps her remains in a river days later, with the help of a friend, Joshua Hancock. Nicholas pleaded guilty to the murder of his wife, whose body was found dismembered in the River Witham in March 2023.
title: UK man stabs wife, then chops her body in over 200 pieces

description: A major highlight of the DC bowling was Ishant Sharma's toe-crushing yorker to Andre Russell that made the swashbuckling batsman fall onto the floor quite awkwardly. By the time Russell could bring his bat down, the stumps were in an amazing state of mess. While walking back, Russell even clapped acknowledging the great delivery by the veteran pacer.
title: Watch: Ishant Sharma talks about 'The yorker that lit up Vizag!'

description: PTI leaders criticize Maryam Nawaz's terrorism claims, blaming PDM. Hasan condemns Sharif family's animosity towards Khyber Pakhtunkhwa. They aim to expose election fraud and reclaim mandates.
title: Pakistan Punjab CM labels Khyber 'corridor of terrorists'

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi attacked on Congress at a Nawada rally, highlighting progress surpassing post-independence achievements. Emphasised bold government initiatives, commitment to eradicating poverty, and empowering rural Bihar. Bihar CM Nitish Kumar echoed rapid development sentiment. BJP's Vivek Thakur contests Nawada seat. NDA campaign in Bihar underway for April polls.
title: 'INDI alliance not able to decide its leader': PM Modi in Bihar

description: PTI's Barrister Gohar Ali Khan dismissed merging with SIC, citing political differences. ECP's ruling prevented SIC from reserved seats. PTI awaits 'bat' symbol return for parliamentary participation and intraparty elections certification.
title: PTI questions legitimacy of postponed elections

description: Reliance Industries, Tata Motors, and Indian Oil Corporation are competing for the government's green hydrogen project in transportation. The project aligns with India's decarbonization goals and aims to address operational challenges.
title: RIL, Tata Motors, IOC key bidders for green hydrogen project

description: Bengaluru police arrested five individuals, including Umashankar and Vinesh, for assaulting Suresh over work pressure. The assault video sparked social media outrage, with users expressing shock over corruption and violence in Bangalore.
title: Angry with work, men hire goons to assault manager

description: Financial educator Ravindra Balu Bharti has been instructed by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) to transfer more than Rs 12 crore, earned through illegitimate means. Bharti must deposit the funds into an interest-bearing Escrow Account in a nationalized bank. Sebi specified that the Escrow Account will hold the amount in Sebi's favour, with no withdrawals permitted without the regulator's consent.
title: Sebi asks this Youtuber to deposit Rs 12 crore

description: CBI investigates the suicide abetment of student J S Sidharthan in Wayanad, who was found hanging in the hostel washroom after being assaulted following a public trial. The probe includes the assault details and the subsequent actions taken by the government.
title: 'Public trial': Student dies by suicide after 2 days of assault

description: Mark Zuckerberg overtakes Elon Musk as the world's third-richest person. Tesla struggles while Meta's stock price soars, reflecting broader trends in the tech industry.
title: Zuckerberg beats Tesla Musk in this 'rich list' for 1st time since 2020

description: Ecommerce, gaming, utilities, and government services dominated India's online transactions in H2 2023. UPI transactions surged, mobile wallets gained popularity, and in-store purchases increased. PoS terminals expanded, with electronic toll collection and mobile payments on the rise.
title: Digital payments in India: What's driving the Big growth

description: Dr.kavithaajay's viral video of a man cutting a papaya instead of a cake on his birthday sparked mixed reactions. Some supported the healthy fruit cake idea, while others expressed disappointment and reluctance to celebrate traditional occasions.
title: Man cutting papaya instead of cake bemuses netizens
BJP Odisha VP Lekhasri Samantasinghar resigns, joins BJD

description: Fixed deposit interest rates: Interest income from FDs is fully taxable and contributes to your overall tax obligation. Since FD interest is considered "income from other sources," Tax Deducted at Source (TDS) is applicable.
title: Top banks offering up to 8.1% interest rates on 1-3 year FDs

description: Top leaders and party workers of Aam Aadmi Party gathered at Jantar Mantar from 11 am on Sunday for a day-long 'Samuhik Upwas' to protest against the arrest of Delhi Chief minister Arvind Kejriwal. Chief minister Bhagwant Mann of AAP-ruled Punjab participated in a joint fast at the village of freedom fighter Bhagat Singh in Khatkar Kalan.
title: AAP leaders hold fast to protest against Kejriwal's arrest

description: Delhi govt orders dry days for elections near Uttar Pradesh border districts. Licensees not compensated. Premises to remain closed on specified dry days including Id-ul-Fitr and Ram Navami.
title: Dry days: No alcohol on these days in April and May

description: Elon Musk, the founder of SpaceX, voiced doubts regarding the existence of extraterrestrial beings, underscoring the necessity of concrete evidence before embracing such a concept. Musk's remarks, delving into the presence of aliens and the feasibility of Mars as a potential colony, provided valuable perspectives on the company's aspirations for exploration beyond the confines of our planet.
title: 'It's like Fermi Paradox': Musk on existence of aliens

description: Australia plans to assign a special adviser to work closely with Israel in ensuring "transparency" during the investigation of an airstrike in Gaza that led to the deaths of seven aid workers, including one Australian. Foreign minister Penny Wong stressed the importance of clear explanations regarding the incident involving aid workers from the World Central Kitchen in the US, who were killed by Israeli forces.
title: Australia to probe Gaza aid workers deaths

description: On April 8, a solar eclipse will darken certain parts of the world, providing a rare view of daytime darkness and the sun's corona for those in its path. Observers will be treated to a unique 'planetary parade' as seven planets - Uranus, Jupiter, Mercury, Venus, Neptune, Saturn, and Mars - make an appearance near the sun during totality.
title: Witness 'planetary parade' on Monday's solar eclipse

description: Rwandans will on Sunday mark 30 years since a genocide orchestrated by Hutu extremists tore apart their country, as neighbours turned on each other in one of the bloodiest massacres of the 20th century. Each year new mass graves are uncovered around the country.
title: Rwanda reflects on 30 years since genocide

description: Prabhas, Amitabh Bachchan, Kamal Haasan and Deepika Padukone's 'Kalki 2898 AD' postponed to May 30 due to Lok Sabha election scheduling clash, aiming for a smoother theatrical run. The sci-fi drama, directed by Nag Ashwin, features a star-studded cast and is touted as one of the most expensive Indian films with extensive VFX.
title: Prabhas, Deepika starrer 'Kalki 2898 AD' postponed to May 30?

description: China's military conducted 'combat patrols' in the South China Sea, coinciding with joint drills by the Philippines, US, Japan, and Australia. The PLA announced 'joint naval and air combat patrols' to manage tensions. US reiterated commitment to protect the Philippines, sparking dissatisfaction from China. Geopolitical tensions rise in the region with competing territorial claims and joint efforts for stability.
title: China conducts military exercises in contested South China Sea

description: New Zealand's government implemented changes to its employment visa program, aiming to address "unsustainable" net migration. The alterations include an English-language requirement and reduced stay for lower-skilled positions. The move follows concerns over record migration levels, potentially impacting housing demand. Despite a slowdown in working-age population growth, the central bank remains cautious about inflationary pressures.
title: New Zealand implements changes to employment visa

description: Virat Kohli's 8th IPL century silenced doubters, but questions cotinue to be asked about his strike rate in the T20 format and RCB's poor performance, as Jos Buttler's century led Rajasthan Royals to victory, pushing RCB down to eighth on the points table. RCB have now lost four out of their five matches this season so far.
title: Pakistan pacer trolls Virat Kohli for 'slowest 100 in IPL'

description: A passenger on an Air New Zealand flight from Auckland to Sydney Airport faced fines and charges after urinating into a cup during a delay in deplaning. The incident, reported by Stuff, involved the man urinating in a cup next to fellow passengers, causing discomfort and disruption. He was fined 600 Australian dollars for offensive behavior affecting safety.
title: Passenger urinates in cup mid-flight, faces fines and charges

description: Smriti Irani challenges INDIA bloc on PM candidate while campaigning for R C Paul Kanagaraj. She questions Congress's contribution to TN, highlights Modi's leadership, and receives a fish gift from fishermen during the campaign.
title: INDIA hugging in Delhi, begging in Kerala, thugging in TN: Smriti

description: Kohli's century re-ignited debates on his T20 World Cup selection, garnering support from various sources, while a few contineud to crtiticise him for scoring at a slow rate.  However, Kohli's 72-ball 113 not out came in a losing cause for RCB against RR, who rode on Jos Buttler's unbeaten ton to overhaul RCB's 183 for 3 for a six-wicket win.
title: 'Think wisely BCCI': Virat's IPL ton rallies support for...

description: Tamil Nadu’s top politicians employ various strategies, from acerbic humor to aggressive campaigning, to sway voters. Each leader has a distinct style and targets different rivals, promising economic growth and development under their leadership.
title: The way they sway: How TN’s top politicians get messages across

description: A private bus from Bengaluru to Gokarna overturned near Holalakere town, resulting in 4 deaths and 30 injuries. 8 individuals are in critical condition. The injured are at Holalakere Taluk Hospital while the deceased are in the mortuary. Residents blame poorly constructed roads for frequent accidents.
title: Bus overturns in Karnataka, four dead, 30 injured

description: One wonders what was the role given to Ajinkya Rahane and skipper Ruturaj Gaikwad and whether the discussion was to score at 116.66 and 123.80, respectively. Of the 120 balls available to a side in T20 cricket, the two batters combined faced 51 of them for 61 runs. That is a strike-rate of 119.60. Unacceptable in modern T20. Especially when you are against a powerhouse batting line-up.
title: IPL 2024: Are anchors still relevant in T20 cricket?

description: Former deputy CM Eshwarappa filed a court caveat in Sagar for Lok Sabha, accusing BJP of blocking Modi's photo use. Yediyurappa's son criticized him for exploiting Hindutva. Eshwarappa rebelled against State BJP.
title: Rebel BJP neta in court: Don’t stop me from using PM Modi pics

description: Reduced RSS presence in Kerala BJP campaign, with BJP taking control of funds and focusing on development to diminish RSS influence. The strategy aims to improve candidate acceptance and voter support in the elections.
title: In Kerala, BJP harps on Modi & devt, keeps RSS at arm’s length

description: The Titans, led by young captain Shubman Gill, have played four matches with two victories and two defeats and need to win against LSG to strengthen their position. With the brilliant performance by its players, especially the express pace of Mayank Yadav, LSG have begun the league well. Gujarat Titans' top-order batter Sai Sudarshan has played well and helped the team put up a big total.
title: All eyes on Mayank Yadav as LSG eye hat-trick of wins

description: In 2014 Mumbai Indians lost five on the trot but still made it to the playoffs. In 2015 they suffered four-straight defeats before going on to clinch the title. In the 2024 edition, they have been slow off the blocks once again having lost their first three. But unlike those two campaigns, things are a bit different this time around.
title: Mumbai Indians, Delhi Capitals look to salvage season

description: Kaspersky warns Indian businesses of increasing ransomware threats, emphasizing the need for robust cybersecurity defenses. The country faces major financial losses due to cyberattacks. Urgent deployment of threat intelligence is crucial.
title: Why Indian businesses need anti-hacking solutions urgently

description: Sundar Pichai emphasized the importance of user feedback, multiple viewpoints, and refining AI models for better products during the 2024 forum keynote.
title: Google CEO on what pushes the company to make its 'products better'

description: Amazon launches Bazaar store in India to compete in fast-fashion market. Offers unbranded products, competes with Meesho, Shopsy, Ajio's Ajio Street. Inspired by global fashion brands. Focuses on premium offerings, user growth, and consumer engagement.
title: Amazon takes on Meesho, Flipkart, & Reliance with Bazaar; offers and more

description: Nikita Pandey's quick thinking using Alexa to scare a monkey impressed Anand Mahindra. Her aspiration to work with him showcases her confidence. Her father's surprise at her newfound fame highlights the family's pride.
title: Mahindra offers job to teen who warded off monkey using Alexa

description: Apple fights to overturn the ITC ban on Apple Watch models, citing flawed patent rulings and concerns over potential misuse of CAD software. The tech giant aims to restore the blood oxygen monitoring feature disabled in the modified versions.
title: Apple argues Masimo had no competing product against its watches

description: Hoarding outside Lucknow's Samajwadi Party HQ urges Eid mourning for Mukhtar Ansari. SP distances itself, removed for code violation. Akhilesh Yadav's Ghazipur visit. Photos of party leaders displayed. Rajendra Chaudhary comments.
title: ‘Mourn Mukhtar, don’t celebrate Eid': Hoarding outside SP HQ

description: In Durjoynagar, police investigate a housewife's suicide linked to intimate photos posted online. No arrests yet, with ongoing questioning. The husband filed a defamation complaint against the accused. Social stigma and fear of family questioning are considered.
title: Housewife ‘hangs self’ after lover posts her photos online
